    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-11-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="372" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Grubb</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-11-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 14,
                            1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 149.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of Mr.
                        Newberry’s No. 152, of the 31st ultimo, reporting the refusal of the Spanish
                        Government to issue its exequatur in favor of Herbert L. Rand, of Illinois,
                        appointed consul of the United States at Ponape, Caroline Islands.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
